args:
After venting his regret at not being chosen for
the Great Twelve, Ebisu escapes. Meanwhile,
Hanabusa is cracking under the pressure,
while Daikokuten remains weighed down by his
complicated friendship with Ebisu. But at least
Mitsuhide seems to have SOME sort of plan...?
That is enough of your mischief.
Oh, is it over? Geez, having a soulpact\nmakes things SO much easier.
I've never known anyone to think of a\nsoulpact in terms of convenience before.
...Huh? W-what have I been doing?\nWhat's going on?!
You mean you don't remember snappin'\nand screamin' about blood and... Hmm.\nYou know what? Probably for the best.
All right, Ebisu. Why'd you go and\nyoink all the New Year's stuff?
You know exactly how important\nthe New Year's events are to us!\nNow return what you have stolen!
Hmph! And how would I know anything\nabout the customs of the Great Twelve?
Let Amaterasu get mad at Daikokuten and\nthe Wyrmclan leaders! That's fine with me!
Hmm. Looks like we're going to need to\nfind some other way to convince him.
Ebisu! Return the gifts this instant\nor my blade will not be stayed!
Ebisu! Give the gifts back or I'll...\nuh...take a nap!
Ebisu! Give 'em back or I'll... Hee hee!
Well, I have no idea what THAT'S about.
Ebisu! Give the gifts back or I will\nhave serious gastrointestinal issues!
Gross. Also, not really my problem\nif you think about it? Meow?
If the new year begins without us having\ndelivered good fortune, you will be facing\na scolding from Lady Amaterasu as well.
If I have to endure a scolding to make\nthis regret go away, then so be it!
You speak of your regret in not\nbecoming one of the Great Twelve?
Of COURSE I speak of that, you fool!\nIt wasn't supposed to be YOU delivering\ngood fortune—it was supposed to be me!
Ebisu, what happened that day was—
BZZZT! Sorry, time's up. Also,\nnot interested. Bye-onara, losers!
Do the words of Ebisu pique your curiosity?
They do, actually. It seems like I'm\nmissing a vital part of the story.
Ebisu claims to have stolen the gifts\nout of regret—but regret for WHAT?
Are you familiar with the Great Twelve?
You speak of the twelve dragons who\nforged soulpacts with the leaders of the\nTwelve Wyrmclans?
The very same. Now, let me tell you the\ntale of how those twelve were chosen.
A competition was held during the\nNew Year's season.
Lady Amaterasu decreed that the first\ntwelve dragons to greet her at the dawn of\nthe new year would be given this honor.
You awarded 'em first-come, first-serve?\nHarsh realm, man.
Indeed. Everyone was quite eager\nto secure one of these positions,\nand Ebisu and myself were no exception.
We were young and wild back then,\nadolescent rivals full of vim and vigor.
Then I take it you won a slot in the\nGreat Twelve and Ebisu didn't?
It was more that I was there when the\ncompetition began, while Ebisu was not.
Why would Ebisu fail to show\nat such an important time?
Felines value their sleep highly. And alas,\nby the time Ebisu awoke, the competition\nwas already decided.
I can't believe he just slept through it.\nThat's, like, the oldest excuse in the book!
So all of this drama is just a big tantrum\nfor his own stupid mistake?
One could certainly see it in that light.\nBut had I gone to wake him that day,\nthings may have been different.
I knew he was not over what happened,\nbut did not understand the true depths\nof his pain until this moment.
I should have noticed sooner. As one of the\nGreat Twelve, it is a disgraceful oversight.
So Ebisu and Daikokuten\nused to be quite close, eh?
Well, there is only one way to move past\nsuch an event. Luckily, it is easily done...
We must cut Ebisu down and remove him \nfrom the equation entirely!
Did you literally miss EVERYTHING\nthat just happened, ya weirdo?!
Looks like ol' Ebisu gave us the slip.
So we have to start over from square one?\nOhhhh... My stomaaach!
(He's buckling under the pressure,\nwhile HE'S still lugging around the\npain of an old, soured friendship.)
(I have a feeling things are about\nto get interesting. Heh heh heh!)
